author: Ralph Emerson
message: Each man has his own vocation; his talent is his call. There is one direction in which all space is open to him.
title: Thought of the day

author: William James
message: To change ones life, start immediately, do it flamboyantly, no exceptions.
title: Thought of the day

author: John F. Kennedy
message: As we express our gratitude, we must never forget that the highest appreciation is not to utter words, but to live by them.
title: Thought of the day

author: Booker Washington
message: The world cares very little about what a man or woman knows; it is what a man or woman is able to do that counts.
title: Thought of the day
